c=\"https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/solar-panel-comparison.png\" width=\"467\" height=\"475\" srcset=\"https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/solar-panel-comparison.png 467w, https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/solar-panel-comparison-295x300.png 295w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px\" title=\"solar panel comparison\" 		class=\"so-widget-image\"/>\n</div>\n\n</div></div></div></div><div id=\"pg-86-1\"  class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\"  data-style=\"{&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;}\" ><div id=\"pgc-86-1-0\"  class=\"panel-grid-cell\"  data-weight=\"0.46213333333333\" ><div id=\"panel-86-1-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-image panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"2\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\" ><div class=\"so-widget-sow-image so-widget-sow-image-default-813df796d9b1\">\n\n<div class=\"sow-image-container\">\n	<img src=\"https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/KinetEco-Residential-Solar-System_LYNDA_11658.jpg\" width=\"792\" height=\"612\" srcset=\"https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/KinetEco-Residential-Solar-System_LYNDA_11658.jpg 792w, https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/KinetEco-Residential-Solar-System_LYNDA_11658-300x232.jpg 300w, https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/KinetEco-Residential-Solar-System_LYNDA_11658-768x593.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 792px) 100vw, 792px\" title=\"KinetEco Residential Solar System_LYNDA_11658\" 		class=\"so-widget-image\"/>\n</div>\n\n</div></div></div><div id=\"pgc-86-1-1\"  class=\"panel-grid-cell\"  data-weight=\"0.53786666666667\" ><div id=\"panel-86-1-1-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"3\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\" ><div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n	<h1>How Solar Works</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<h6>Particles of light (photons) from the sun hit solar panels and are converted into electrons of DC electricity inside the photovoltaic cells.</h6>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h6>The electrons flow out of the solar panels and into an inverter where they are converted into AC power that can be used in your home.</h6>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h6>A net energy meter tracks all the power produced by the solar system.</h6>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h6>At night, or on cloudy days, youll consume energy from the grid, as normal.</h6>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h6>During the day, under optimal conditions, youll consume electricity directly from the sun, as its generated.</h6>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h6>Excess solar energy that you do not use goes back into the electrical grid, and is credited to your utility bill.</h6>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n</div></div></div></div><div id=\"pg-86-2\"  class=\"panel-grid panel-no-style\"  data-style=\"{&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;,&quot;cell_alignment&quot;:&quot;flex-start&quot;}\" ><div id=\"pgc-86-2-0\"  class=\"panel-grid-cell\"  data-weight=\"1\" ><div id=\"panel-86-2-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"4\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\" ><div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\n	<p></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This is a fictitiouscompanycreated by<a href=\"http://linkedin.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">LinkedInCorporation</a>, or its affiliates,solely for the creation and development ofeducational training materials. Any resemblance to realproducts or servicesis purely coincidental. Information provided about theproducts or servicesis also fictitious and should not be construed as representative of actualproducts or serviceson the market in a similarproduct or servicecategory.</p></div>\n</div></div></div></div></div>', 'So