(109, 1, '2017-01-28 02:06:41', '2017-01-28 02:06:41', 'KinetEco, Inc. may be a large international company on the surface, butat heart, we\'re a grassroots environmental group thatbelieves in the power of community. We know that passion for the environment is cultured at a young age. As such, we feel it\'s our responsibilityto help educate children about alternative energy. Every year, our corporate offices hold various events for the youth in our communities. Recently, our San Diego office sponsoreda solar energy art contest for middleschools in the area, and the response was overwhelming. Over 300 children submitted their paintings, drawings, and computer-drafted artwork for a chance to win an Apple Watch. Our employee judges had a difficult time choosing the winners, but ultimately narrowed it down to three strong submissions. Here are the wonderful art piecesthat took home the big prize this year:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_110\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-110 size-medium\" src=\"https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/solar-drawing-452479361-300x212.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" /> April Donnelly, 7th grade, Oak Valley Middle School[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_111\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-111 size-medium\" src=\"https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/solar-drawing-135519715-300x300.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /> Juan Torres, 8th grade, Bernardo Heights Middle School[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_112\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-112 size-medium\" src=\"https://kinetecoinc.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/solar-drawing-142028870-300x212.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" /> Saanvi Gupta, 6th grade, Lewis Middle School[/caption]', 'Solar art contest winners', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'solar-art-contest-winners', '', '', '2017-01-28 02:09:10', '2017-01-28 02:09:10', '', 0, 'https://kinetecoinc.com/?p=1